      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on blueberry bushes can be caused by both nitrogen deficiency and soil pH issues, so testing is key. First, check your soil pH; blueberries prefer acidic soil, generally between 4.5 and 5.5. If the pH is too high, the plant might struggle to absorb nutrients, even if they are present. A soil test will tell you exactly what your soil needs to remain healthy.",
