    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been digging around the roots a bit to check for pests or anything weird in the soil, but i dont see any bugs or anything. it just feels like something is wrong underneath the surface. what else should i look for in the dirt itself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since you've checked for visible pests, next, examine the soil structure for compaction or drainage issues. Dig down a bit deeper to see if the dirt is overly dense or if water pools around the roots after rain. Poor drainage can suffocate the roots, mimicking nutrient problems, and it's a common subsurface issue. You can also check for signs of root rot, which might appear as soft, dark, or mushy roots.",
